Note: ===== ASTRONOMICAL UTILITY FUNCTIONS =====

Process called "determine_moon_phase_name" that takes days as Float returns String:
    If days is less than 1.84566:
        Return "New Moon"
    Otherwise if days is less than 5.53699:
        Return "Waxing Crescent"
    Otherwise if days is less than 9.22831:
        Return "First Quarter"
    Otherwise if days is less than 12.91963:
        Return "Waxing Gibbous"
    Otherwise if days is less than 16.61096:
        Return "Full Moon"
    Otherwise if days is less than 20.30228:
        Return "Waning Gibbous"
    Otherwise if days is less than 23.99361:
        Return "Last Quarter"
    Otherwise:
        Return "Waning Crescent"

Process called "calculate_moon_illumination" that takes days as Float returns Float:
    Let phase_angle be (days times 2.0 times 3.14159) divided by 29.5305882
    Let illumination be (1.0 plus cosine of phase_angle) divided by 2.0
    Return illumination times 100.0

Process called "calculate_solar_position" that takes jdn as Integer and latitude as Float and longitude as Float returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Simplified solar position calculation
    Let sunrise_hour be 6.0 plus (longitude divided by 15.0)  Note: Rough approximation
    Let sunset_hour be 18.0 plus (longitude divided by 15.0)
    
    Note: Adjust for latitude (simplified)
    Let latitude_adjustment be (latitude minus 45.0) divided by 90.0
    Set sunrise_hour to sunrise_hour minus latitude_adjustment
    Set sunset_hour to sunset_hour plus latitude_adjustment
    
    Return dictionary with "sunrise_hour" as sunrise_hour, "sunset_hour" as sunset_hour

Process called "convert_decimal_hour_to_time" that takes hour as Float returns Time:
    Let whole_hour be hour as Integer
    Let minute_decimal be (hour minus whole_hour) times 60.0
    Let whole_minute be minute_decimal as Integer
    Let second_decimal be (minute_decimal minus whole_minute) times 60.0
    Let whole_second be second_decimal as Integer
    
    Return Time with:
        hour as whole_hour
        minute as whole_minute
        second as whole_second

Process called "determine_zodiac_sign_from_date" that takes month as Integer and day as Integer returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Western zodiac sign determination
    If month is equal to 1:
        If day is less than 20:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Capricorn" and symbol as "♑" and element as "Earth" and quality as "Cardinal" and planet as "Saturn"
        Otherwise:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Aquarius" and symbol as "♒" and element as "Air" and quality as "Fixed" and planet as "Uranus"
    
    Otherwise if month is equal to 2:
        If day is less than 19:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Aquarius" and symbol as "♒" and element as "Air" and quality as "Fixed" and planet as "Uranus"
        Otherwise:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Pisces" and symbol as "♓" and element as "Water" and quality as "Mutable" and planet as "Neptune"
    
    Otherwise if month is equal to 3:
        If day is less than 21:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Pisces" and symbol as "♓" and element as "Water" and quality as "Mutable" and planet as "Neptune"
        Otherwise:
            Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Aries" and symbol as "♈" and element as "Fire" and quality as "Cardinal" and planet as "Mars"
    
    Note: Simplified - would continue for all 12 signs
    Otherwise:
        Return create_zodiac_info with name as "Aries" and symbol as "♈" and element as "Fire" and quality as "Cardinal" and planet as "Mars"

Process called "create_zodiac_info" that takes name as String and symbol as String and element as String and quality as String and planet as String returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Return dictionary with:
        "sign_name" as name
        "sign_symbol" as symbol
        "element" as element
        "quality" as quality
        "ruling_planet" as planet
        "date_range" as name with message " season"

Process called "create_meteor_shower" that takes name as String and peak_date as Date returns MeteorShower:
    Return MeteorShower with:
        name as name
        peak_date as peak_date
        radiant_constellation as get_radiant_constellation with name as name
        peak_rate_per_hour as get_peak_rate with name as name
        visibility_conditions as "Best viewed after midnight in dark skies"

Process called "get_radiant_constellation" that takes shower_name as String returns String:
    Match shower_name:
        When "Quadrantids":
            Return "Boötes"
        When "Lyrids":
            Return "Lyra"
        When "Perseids":
            Return "Perseus"
        When "Orionids":
            Return "Orion"
        When "Leonids":
            Return "Leo"
        When "Geminids":
            Return "Gemini"
        Otherwise:
            Return "Unknown"

Process called "get_peak_rate" that takes shower_name as String returns Integer:
    Match shower_name:
        When "Quadrantids":
            Return 80
        When "Lyrids":
            Return 18
        When "Perseids":
            Return 60
        When "Orionids":
            Return 25
        When "Leonids":
            Return 15
        When "Geminids":
            Return 75
        Otherwise:
            Return 10

Note: ===== PLACEHOLDER ASTRONOMICAL CALCULATIONS =====
Note: These would contain complex astronomical algorithms in production

Process called "calculate_spring_equinox" that takes year as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Spring equinox typically occurs around March 20-21
    Let day be 20 plus ((year minus 2000) modulo 4)
    Return create_date with year as year and month as 3 and day as day

Process called "calculate_summer_solstice" that takes year as Integer returns Date:
    Note: Summer solstice typically occurs around June 20-21
    Let day be 21 plus ((year minus 2000) modulo 4)
    Return create_date with year as year and month as 6 and day as day

